277. focus ipse ‘the ordinary hearth itself) They used to have no special ovens for baking.—Some ‘broken tiles’ (legula quassa ; sor quassa see V. 460) were spread on the warni hearth-sssone3 on these was laid the dough (panis), covered with an earthenware pot (called testu), over which the hot coals were placed. African tribes still cook elephants' feet, and other delicacies, in this manner.
